<doc id="1187989" wikidata="Q2837866" url="?curid=1187989" title="Plymouth, Florida">
<text>Plymouth is an unincorporated area in Orange County, Florida, United States, northwest of downtown Apopka along US 441 (SR 500) (Orange Blossom Trail), at the intersection with Plymouth-Sorrento Road. It features the Pinsly Railroad Company&#x27;s Florida headquarters and part of the Florida Central Railroad. It is statistically part of the Greater Orlando area.

==Notable person==
*Warren Sapp, professional football player, Tampa Bay Buccaneers and Oakland Raiders.

