<doc id="1188116" wikidata="Q5287790" url="?curid=1188116" title="Dodds, Ohio">
<text>Dodds is an unincorporated community in eastern Clearcreek Township, Warren County, Ohio, United States. It was formerly on the Cincinnati, Lebanon and Northern Railway.

==History==
A post office called Dodds was established in 1881, and remained in operation until 1901. The Dodds family had settled the area in the early 19th century.

